# gh

> Work seamlessly with GitHub from the command-line
> Some subcommands such as `gh config` have their own usage documentation
> More information: https://cli.github.com/

- Clone a GitHub repository locally:

`gh repo clone {string value: owner}/{string value: repository}`

- Create a new issue:

`gh issue create`

- View and filter the open issues of the current repository:

`gh issue list`

- View an issue in the default web browser:

`gh issue view --web {string value: issue_number}`

- Create a pull request:

`gh pr create`

- View a pull request in the default web browser:

`gh pr view --web {string value: pr_number}`

- Check out a specific pull request locally:

`gh pr checkout {string value: pr_number}`

- Check the status of a repository's pull requests:

`gh pr status`
